snippet: A bizarre cargo of more than 80 exotic reptiles, including four horned vipers and an iguana, attracted the attention of an alert customs official at Frankfurt Airport this week.
abstract: Customs officials at Frankfurt Airport in Germany find cargo of more than 80 exotic reptiles; owner of cargo, 44-year-old man from Mexico, is under investigation to determine whether he violated laws on protection of endangered species and treatment of animals.
lead_paragraph: A bizarre cargo of more than 80 exotic reptiles, including four horned vipers and an iguana, attracted the attention of an alert customs official at Frankfurt Airport this week.

headline.main: Germany: The Flight of the Iguana
headline.print_headline: Germany: The Flight of the Iguana
